{"serial": "61035", "department_serial": 56, "code": "AP6163", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Introduction to Physical Oceanography", "ch": "物理海洋學概論"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Wang, Li-Chiao"], "ch": ["王儷樵"]}, "credits": 2, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 4, "session": ["7", "8"]}, "loc": {"building": "S1", "room": "804"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": -1, "department": {"ch": "大氣科學學系", "en": "Department of Atmospheric Physics"}, "system": {"ch": "博士班", "en": "Doctoral Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "英語", "en": "English"}, "card": {"ch": "不使用", "en": "None"}, "assigned": 0, "selected": 12, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "海洋對大氣的交互作用在全球氣候系統中扮演著重要角色，故理解海洋物理性質有助於氣候研究。本課程我們結合課堂講座與文獻探討，引領學生了解海洋動力機制與大尺度海氣耦合的物理過程。", "en": "The feedbacks of the ocean to the atmosphere play a substantial role in the global climate system. Therefore, understanding the physical oceanic properties is of key importance in climatic research. In this class, a general description will be given regarding the physical-oceanographic processes, theories, and measurements. The dynamics of large-scale ocean-atmosphere coupling will also be discussed."}, "outline": {"ch": "*物理海洋概論\n*海洋的結構\n*海洋的物理性質\n*海洋對於大氣的反應\n*深層海洋環流\n*波浪\n*潮汐\n*專題演講\n*電影欣賞\n*文獻報告", "en": "1.Introduction\n2.The physical settings\n3.The properties of the sea water\n4.Winds and responses of ocean\n5.Deep circulations\n6.Waves\n7.Tides\n8.Invited Talk\n9.Movie Time\n10.Paper Report"}, "textbook": {"ch": "物理海洋學概論, Robert H. Stewart.\n海洋學概論第五版, Paul R. Pinet.", "en": "Introduction to Physical Oceanography, Robert H. Stewart.\nInvitation to Oceanography, 5th edition, by Paul R. Pinet."}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "70%", "en": "70%"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "講授\n研討\n\n個別指導", "en": ["Lecture", "Seminar", "", "Individual Instruction"]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "期中考試 35％\n期末口頭報告與回答問題 35％\n期末報告提問 20％\n課堂討論 10％", "en": "Written test (closed-book) 35％\nOral presentation and question